<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n41036b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n41" href="#n41036b">N41 (VI.B.33)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n41all.htm#n41036b"> 36(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> 7 yrs absence / presumes death</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">If the husband or wife has been continuously <mark>absent from the accused during the seven years preceding</mark> the second marriage, and has not been heard of by the accused during that time, the accused is entitled to <mark>assume</mark> that his or her wife or husband <mark>is dead</mark>, and to re-marry. <small> Maud I. Crofts, <a name="MICW" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#MICW"><cite title="source">Women under English Law</cite></a>, 1st ed. (1925) 31</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
